tm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061026194057/https://www.un.org/Overview/growth.htm|archive-date=26 October 2006|title=Growth in United Nations membership (1945\u20132005)|publisher=United Nations|accessdate=2006-10-30|date=2006-07-03}}</ref> Difficulties faced by Greece after the war in quelling a communist rebellion, along with [[Turkish Straits crisis|demands]] by the Soviet Union for military bases in the [[Turkish Straits]], prompted the United States to declare the [[Truman Doctrine]] in 1947. The doctrine enunciated American intentions to guarantee the security of Turkey and Greece, and resulted in significant U.S. military and economic support.<ref name=\"Truman Doctrine\" >{{cite book|title=Outposts and Allies: U.S. Army Logistics in the Cold War, 1945-1953|first=James A|last=Huston|publisher=Susquehanna University Press|location= |year=1988|isbn=0-941664-84-8|url=https://books.google.com/?id=ID4E3Lm8TsgC&pg=PA198&lpg=PA198&dq=turkey+cold+war|page=198}}</ref> This support manifested in the establishment of a clandestine [[stay-behind]] army, denoted the \"[[Counter-Guerrilla]]\", under [[Operation Gladio]]. After participating with United Nations forces in the [[Korean War]], Turkey joined the [[North Atlantic Treaty Organization]] in 1952.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nato.int/cps/en/natolive/topics_52044.htm |title=Member countries |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=March 10, 2016  |website=nato.int |publisher=[[NATO]] |access-date=August 24, 2016 |quote=}}</ref>\n\nRelations between the countries began to deteriorate in 2003 as Turkey refused to allow the United States to use [[Incirlik Air Base]] for the [[Iraq War|invasion of Iraq]], a process that intensified following the failed [[2016 Turkish coup d'\u00e9tat attempt|coup d'\u00e9tat attempt]] in Turkey in July 2016 as the country\u2032s foreign policy has gradually re-orientated towards seeking partnerships with other powers such as [[Russia]].<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2018-08-03/u-s-sanctions-against-nato-ally-turkey-puts-ties-at-crossroads U.S. Sanctions Against NATO Ally Turkey Put Ties at Crossroads] Bloomberg, 3 August 2018.</ref><ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/apr/11/turkey-ever-closer-ties-with-russia-leave-us-lacking-key-ally-on-syria Turkey's ever-closer ties with Russia leave US lacking key ally on Syria] The Guardian, 11 April 2018.</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Yegin|first=Mehmet|title=Turkey-U.S. Relations: Towards a Multidimentional Partnership (May 2013)|url=https://www.academia.edu/5461662}}</ref>\n\nA 2017 survey conducted by the [[Pew Research Center]] showed 79% of Turks had a negative view of the United States, with only 18% having a positive view.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.pewglobal.org/2017/06/26/tarnished-american-brand/ |title = Trump Unpopular Worldwide, American Image Suffers|date = 2017-06-26}}</ref> The same study also showed only 11% of Turks had confidence in the current US leader, President Donald Trump,<ref>{{cite news|title=Amid tension, Trump and Turkey's Erdogan agree to strengthen ties|url=http://www.muslimglobal.com/2017/09/amid-tension-trump-and-turkeys-erdogan.html|accessdate=9 September 2017|publisher=Muslim Global}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.pewglobal.org/2017/06/26/u-s-image-suffers-as-publics-around-world-question-trumps-leadership/ | title=Trump Unpopular Worldwide, American Image Suffers| date=2017-06-26}}</ref>  with 82% having no confidence in him.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.pewglobal.org/2017/06/26/worldwide-few-confident-in-trump-or-his-policies/ |title = Trump Unpopular Worldwide, American Image Suffers|date = 2017-06-26}}</ref>\n\n==Country comparison==\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\"\n|-\n! Common name !! [[Turkey]] !! [[United States]]\n|-\n! Official name !! Republic of Turkey!! United States of America\n|-\n| Coat of arms\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | \n| style=\"text-align:center\" | [[File:Great